<db:section xml:id="setControlType">
<db:title>[since 4.3] void QSizePolicy::setControlType(QSizePolicy::ControlType <db:emphasis>type</db:emphasis>)</db:title>
<db:para>Sets the control type associated with the widget for which this size policy applies to <db:code role="parameter">type</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:para>The control type specifies the type of the widget for which this size policy applies. It is used by some styles, notably QMacStyle, to insert proper spacing between widgets. For example, the Mac OS X Aqua guidelines specify that push buttons should be separated by 12 pixels, whereas vertically stacked radio buttons only require 6 pixels.</db:para>
<db:para>This function was introduced in Qt 4.3.</db:para>
